 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "atomic-triumph",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Linear Bivariate BMM with calibration of Coleman toy models.\n",
    "\n",
    "The best way to learn Taweret is to use it. You can run, modify and experiment with this notebook [here.](https://mybinder.org/v2/gh/danOSU/Taweret/c2d8fd3ce3d74a5891d51adb5afc0afa0b503127?urlpath=lab%2Ftree%2Fdocs%2Fsource%2Fnotebooks%2FLinear_BMM_with_cdf_function_for_coleman_models.ipynb)\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "careful-kitchen",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The models can be found in Coleman Thesis : https://go.exlibris.link/3fVZCfhl\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook shows how to use the Bayesian model mixing package **Taweret** for a toy problem. \n",
    "\n",
    "**Author : Dan Liyanage**\n",
    "\n",
    "Date : 11/13/2022"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "id": "emotional-foundation",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import sys\n",
    "\n",
    "# You will have to change the following imports depending on where you have \n",
    "# the packages installed\n",
    "\n",
    "# If using binder please uncomment the following.\n",
    "sys.path.append(\"/home/jovyan/\")\n",
    "\n",
    "#sys.path.append(\"/Users/dananjayaliyanage/git/Taweret\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# For plotting\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "sns.set_context('poster')\n",
    "# To define priors. (uncoment if not using default priors)\n",
    "#import bilby\n",
    "\n",
    "# For other operations\n",
    "import numpy as np"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "id": "generous-confidentiality",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Import models with a predict method\n",
    "from Taweret.models import coleman_models as toy_models\n",
    "\n",
    "m1 = toy_models.coleman_model_1()\n",
    "m2 = toy_models.coleman_model_2()\n",
    "truth = toy_models.coleman_truth()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "id": "stainless-stations",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "g = np.linspace(-1,9,10)\n",
    "plot_g = np.linspace(-1,9,100)\n",
    "true_output = truth.evaluate(plot_g)\n",
    "exp_data = truth.evaluate(g)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "prime-following",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. The models and the experimental data."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "mexican-pipeline",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Truth\n",
    " \n",
    "$f(x) = 2-0.1(x-4)^2$, where $x \\in [-1, 9]$\n",
    "\n",
    "Model 1\n",
    "\n",
    "$f_1(x,\\theta)= 0.5(x+\\theta)-2$    , where $\\theta \\in [1, 6]$\n",
    "\n",
    "Model 2\n",
    "\n",
    "$f_2(x,\\theta)= -0.5(x-\\theta) + 3.7$   , where $\\theta \\in [-2, 3]$\n",
    "\n",
    "Experimental data \n",
    "\n",
    "sampled from the Truth with a fixed standard deviation of 0.3\n",
    "\n",
    "\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "id": "expired-dryer",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 2000x500 with 2 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "sns.set_context('notebook')\n",
    "fig, axs = plt.subplots(1,2,figsize=(20,5))\n",
    "prior_ranges = [(1,6), (-2,3)]\n",
    "for i in range(0,2):\n",
    "    ax = axs.flatten()[i]\n",
    "    ax.plot(plot_g, true_output[0], label='truth', color='black')\n",
    "    ax.errorbar(g,exp_data[0],exp_data[1], fmt='o', label='experimental data', color='r')\n",
    "    ax.legend()\n",
    "    ax.set_ylim(-2,4)\n",
    "    for value in np.linspace(*prior_ranges[i],10):\n",
    "        if i==0:\n",
    "            predict_1 = m1.evaluate(plot_g, value)\n",
    "            ax.plot(plot_g, predict_1[0])\n",
    "            ax.set_ylabel(r'$f_1(x)$')\n",
    "        if i==1:\n",
    "            predict_2 = m2.evaluate(plot_g, value)\n",
    "            ax.plot(plot_g, predict_2[0])      \n",
    "            ax.set_ylabel(r'$f_2(x)$')    \n",
    "    ax.set_xlabel('x') \n",
    "    \n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "hydraulic-resident",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "##  2. Choose a Mixing method"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "id": "antique-cooking",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "cdf mixing function has 2 free parameter(s)\n",
      "Warning : Default prior is set to {'cdf_0': Uniform(minimum=0, maximum=1, name='cdf_0', latex_label='cdf_0', unit=None, boundary=None), 'cdf_1': Uniform(minimum=0, maximum=1, name='cdf_1', latex_label='cdf_1', unit=None, boundary=None)}\n",
      "To change the prior use `set_prior` method\n",
      "Using default priors for model 1\n",
      "{'model1_0': Uniform(minimum=1, maximum=6, name='model1_0', latex_label='model1_0', unit=None, boundary=None)}\n",
      "Using default priors for model 2\n",
      "{'model2_0': Uniform(minimum=-2, maximum=3, name='model2_0', latex_label='model2_0', unit=None, boundary=None)}\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Mixing method\n",
    "from Taweret.mix.bivariate_linear import BivariateLinear as BL\n",
    "\n",
    "models= {'model1':m1,'model2':m2}\n",
    "mix_model = BL(models_dic=models, method='cdf', nargs_model_dic={'model1':1, 'model2':1})"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "id": "825516bc",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "{'cdf_0': Normal(mu=0, sigma=1, name='cdf_0', latex_label='cdf_0', unit=None, boundary=None),\n",
       " 'cdf_1': Normal(mu=0, sigma=1, name='cdf_1', latex_label='cdf_1', unit=None, boundary=None),\n",
       " 'model1_0': Uniform(minimum=1, maximum=6, name='model1_0', latex_label='model1_0', unit=None, boundary=None),\n",
       " 'model2_0': Uniform(minimum=-2, maximum=3, name='model2_0', latex_label='model2_0', unit=None, boundary=None)}"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 6,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "## uncoment to change the prior from the default\n",
    "import bilby \n",
    "\n",
    "priors = bilby.core.prior.PriorDict()\n",
    "priors['cdf_0'] = bilby.core.prior.Normal(0, 1, name=\"cdf_0\")\n",
    "priors['cdf_1'] = bilby.core.prior.Normal(0, 1, name=\"cdf_1\")\n",
    "mix_model.set_prior(priors)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
